# Cursor Rules Management Guide

Based on [Sashido's self-improving rules](https://www.sashido.io/en/blog/cursor-self-improving-rules). Use this file to teach Cursor how to process, format, and locate other rules.

## Rule Structure Format

Every cursor rule must follow this metadata and content structure:

````markdown
---
description: Short description of the rule's purpose
globs: optional/path/pattern/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---
# Rule Title

Main content explaining the rule with markdown formatting.

1. Step-by-step instructions
2. Code examples
3. Guidelines
````

## File Organization

### Required Location

All cursor rule files **must** be placed in:

```
PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/rules/
```

### Directory Structure

```
syntheteria/
├── .cursor/
│   └── rules/
│       ├── cursor-rules.mdc      # This file
│       ├── self-improvement.mdc
│       ├── prd-yolo-execution.mdc
│       └── your-rule-name.mdc
├── AGENTS.md
├── docs/
└── src/
```

### Naming Conventions

- Use **kebab-case** for all filenames
- Always use **.mdc** extension
- Make names **descriptive** of the rule's purpose
- Examples: `typescript-style.mdc`, `ecs-patterns.mdc`, `radial-menu.mdc`

## Content Guidelines

### Writing Effective Rules

1. **Be specific and actionable** — Provide clear instructions
2. **Include code examples** — Show both good and bad practices
3. **Reference existing files** — Use `@filename` or path references
4. **Keep it focused** — One rule per concern/pattern
5. **Add context** — Explain why the rule exists

### Project-Specific Conventions

- **Systems own logic** — Pure functions in `src/systems/`; no logic in TSX
- **Config over code** — Tuning in JSON under `src/config/` or `config/`
- **Named exports only** — No `export default`
- **Crash on missing assets** — Never silent fallback; see [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)

## Rule Categories

- **Meta**: `cursor-rules.mdc`, `self-improvement.mdc`
- **Execution**: `prd-yolo-execution.mdc` (long-running YOLO execution; source of truth = Ralph PRD in ralph/projects/syntheteria-1-0/)
- **Code style**: TypeScript, React Native / R3F, ECS patterns
- **Architecture**: `docs/technical/`, `docs/design/`

## Best Practices

### Rule Creation Checklist

- [ ] File placed in `.cursor/rules/`
- [ ] Filename uses kebab-case with `.mdc` extension
- [ ] Includes proper frontmatter (description, globs, alwaysApply)
- [ ] Contains clear title and sections
- [ ] References relevant project files or docs when useful
- [ ] Follows [cursor-rules.mdc](.cursor/rules/cursor-rules.mdc) structure

### Maintenance

- **Review regularly** — Keep rules in sync with codebase and docs
- **Cross-reference** — Link related rules and `docs/AGENTS.md`
- **Update after refactors** — When structure or patterns change, update rules
